name: Ledyba
flavorText: These very cowardly Pokémon join together and use Reflect to protect their nest.

name: Ledian
flavorText: It flies through the night sky, sprinkling sparkly dust. According to some, if that dust sticks to you, good things will happen to you.

attackEntries.name: Swift
attackEntries.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Shuckle
flavorText: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

attackEntries.name: Guard Press
attackEntries.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.

name: Roselia
flavorText: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.

attackEntries.name: Trip Over
attackEntries.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Roserade
flavorText: The poison in its right hand is quick acting. The poison in its left hand is slow acting. Both are life threatening.

attackEntries.name: Poison Ring
attackEntries.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Cacnea
flavorText: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.

name: Cacturne
flavorText: It lives in deserts. It becomes active at night when it hunts for prey exhausted from the desert's heat.

attackEntries.name: Spike Rend
attackEntries.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Chespin
flavorText: Eating lots of berries makes the bark shell that covers Chespin's head and body grow sturdier.

name: Quilladin
flavorText: It can send a trailer flying with a tackle. It's numb to pain, so even violent collisions don't faze it.

name: Chesnaught
flavorText: Its gentle disposition would have it avoid conflict, but it gives opponents a thrashing with its thorned fists when the situation calls for it.

attackEntries.name: Needle Lariat
attackEntries.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack, do 80 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

name: Scatterbug
flavorText: This Pokémon scatters poisonous powder to repel enemies. It will eat different plants depending on where it lives.

name: Spewpa
flavorText: Spewpa doesn't live in a fixed location. It roams where it pleases across the fields and mountains, building up the energy it needs to evolve.

attackEntries.name: Signs of Evolution
attackEntries.text: Put a random card that evolves from Spewpa from your deck into your hand.

name: Vivillon
flavorText: This Pokémon was born in a land where flowers bloom. It scatters colorful, toxic scales from its wings during battle.

attackEntries.name: Vivid Powder
attackEntries.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned and Asleep.

name: Buzzwole
flavorText: Buzzwole goes around showing off its abnormally swollen muscles. It is one kind of Ultra Beast.

attackEntries.name: Ground Beat
attackEntries.text: If your opponent has gotten exactly 1 points, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Gossifleur
flavorText: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.

name: Eldegoss
flavorText: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.

attackEntries.name: Float Up
attackEntries.text: You may shuffle this Pokémon and all attached cards into your deck.

abilityEntries.name: Soothing Wind
abilityEntries.text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Energy attached recovers from all Special Conditions and can't be affected by any Special Conditions.

attackEntries.name: Energized Leaves
attackEntries.text: If the amount of Energy attached to both Active Pokémon is 5 or more, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Alolan Marowak
flavorText: The cursed flames that light up the bone carried by this Pokémon are said to cause both mental and physical pain that will never fade.

attackEntries.name: Fiery Bone
attackEntries.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Reshiram
flavorText: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

attackEntries.name: Blue Flare
attackEntries.text: Discard 2 {R} Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Litleo
flavorText: The more a Litleo trains its body and spirit by battling mighty enemies, the hotter its mane will grow.

name: Pyroar
flavorText: The females of a pride work together to bring down prey. It's thanks to them that their pride doesn't starve.

name: Oricorio
flavorText: This form of Oricorio has sipped red nectar. It whips up blazing flames as it moves to the steps of its passionate dance.

attackEntries.name: Inspiring Dance
attackEntries.text: During your next turn, attacks used by your Pokémon do +20 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attackEntries.name: Singe
attackEntries.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

attackEntries.name: Pop-Punk
attackEntries.text: Discard 3 {R} Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Scorbunny
flavorText: Fire energy gathers in the pads of its feet, raising their temperature. Once hot, Scorbunny's footpads can deal heavy damage to opponents.

name: Raboot
flavorText: While it prides itself on its varied kicking moves, it can also deliver powerful headbutts once its flames have heated up its forehead.

name: Cinderace
flavorText: Using a ball that it made out of flames, Cinderace blinds its opponents and keeps them at bay.

attackEntries.name: Fireball Shot
attackEntries.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Hearthflame Mask Ogerpon
flavorText: In this form, it draws on the power of fire. It spears its enemies with thorn-covered ivy.

attackEntries.name: Hearthflame Dance
attackEntries.text: Flip a coin. If heads, take 2 {R} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Alolan Vulpix
flavorText: In hot weather, this Pokémon makes ice shards with its six tails and sprays them around to cool itself off.

attackEntries.name: Binding Snow
attackEntries.text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't take any Energy from their Energy Zone to attach to their Active Pokémon.

name: Galarian Mr. Mime
flavorText: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It'll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.

name: Galarian Mr. Rime
flavorText: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.

attackEntries.name: Triple Spin
attackEntries.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

name: Delibird
flavorText: It always carries its food with it, wherever it goes. If attacked, it throws its food at the opponent.

attackEntries.name: Box of Surprises
attackEntries.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 70 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon. If tails, heal 30 damage from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Mudkip
flavorText: When it uses its large tail fin, it picks up speed rapidly in the water. It is strong in spite of its small size.

name: Marshtomp
flavorText: It is at its best when on muddy ground that offers poor footing. It quickly overwhelms opponents that are bogged down and unable to move.

name: Swampert
flavorText: Swampert's arms are rock-hard. With one swing, they can batter down Swampert's foes. This Pokémon makes its nest on beautiful beaches.

attackEntries.name: Large Whirlpool
attackEntries.text: Discard a random Energy from among the Energy attached to all Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Mega Swampert ex
flavorText: Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing, it can break an enormous boulder into pieces.

attackEntries.name: Strong-Armed Destroyer
attackEntries.text: Discard 2 random Energy from among the Energy attached to all Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Vanillite
flavorText: Supposedly, this Pokémon was born from an icicle. It spews out freezing air at −58 degrees Fahrenheit to make itself more comfortable.

name: Vanillish
flavorText: It blasts enemies with cold air reaching −148 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing them solid. But it spares their lives afterward—it's a kind Pokémon.

name: Vanilluxe
flavorText: People believe this Pokémon formed when two Vanillish stuck together. Its body temperature is roughly 21 degrees Fahrenheit.

attackEntries.name: Sweets Relay
attackEntries.text: If 1 of your Pokémon used Sweets Relay during your last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Cryogonal
flavorText: Cryogonal uses its chains of ice to constrict its opponents and then flash-freezes them where they stand.

attackEntries.name: Frozen Lock
attackEntries.text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Item cards from their hand.

name: Amaura
flavorText: Amaura is an ancient Pokémon that has gone extinct. Specimens of this species can sometimes be found frozen in ice.

name: Aurorus
flavorText: When gripped by rage, Aurorus will emanate freezing air, covering everything around it in ice.

attackEntries.name: Hail Prison
attackEntries.text: Discard Water2 {W} Energy from this Pokémon. Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Chewtle
flavorText: A popular game among children is to lift up sticks that Chewtle have bitten onto to see whose Chewtle can hang on the longest.

name: Drednaw
flavorText: Drednaw lurks along the shoreline. When prey come to drink water, Drednaw stretches its neck out and chomps down on them.

name: Cramorant
flavorText: Cramorant takes advantage of Arrokuda's frantic thrashing to help spit Arrokuda out at high speed.

attackEntries.name: Spit-Out Shot
attackEntries.text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Arrokuda
flavorText: After it's eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That's when Cramorant swallows it up.

name: Barraskewda
flavorText: It spins its tail fins to propel itself, surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.

name: Wellspring Mask Ogerpon
flavorText: In this form, it draws on the power of water. It attacks unrelentingly with kicks and ivy strikes.

attackEntries.name: Wellspring Dance
attackEntries.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack also does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity can build and cause lightning storms.

attackEntries.name: Thunder Jolt
attackEntries.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Alolan Raichu
flavorText: This Pokémon rides on its tail while it uses its psychic powers to levitate. It attacks with star-shaped thunderbolts.

abilityEntries.name: Surge Surfer
abilityEntries.text: If a Stadium is in play, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.

attackEntries.name: Thunder Spear
attackEntries.text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Zapdos
flavorText: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon. It's said that when Zapdos rubs its feathers together, lightning will fall immediately after.

attackEntries.name: Heavy Thunder
attackEntries.text: 1 other Pokémon (either yours or your opponent's) is chosen at random 1 time. Do 100 damage to the chosen Pokémon.

name: Plusle
flavorText: This Pokémon absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out the electricity stored inside its body to create noises.

attackEntries.name: Electric Tail
attackEntries.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Minun
flavorText: Its dislike of water makes it take shelter under the eaves of houses in rain. It uses pom-poms made of sparks for cheering.

attackEntries.name: Buddy Spark
attackEntries.text: If Plusle is on your Bench, this attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Toxel
flavorText: This selfish, attention-seeking Pokémon stores poison and electricity in two different sacs inside its body.

attackEntries.name: Damaging Spark
attackEntries.text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has damage on it.

name: Tadbulb
flavorText: It floats using the electricity stored in its body. When thunderclouds are around, Tadbulb will float higher off the ground.

attackEntries.name: Charge
attackEntries.text: Take a {L} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

name: Bellibolt
flavorText: What appear to be eyeballs are actually organs for discharging the electricity generated by Bellibolt's belly-button dynamo.

name: Galarian Ponyta
flavorText: This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.

name: Galarian Rapidash
flavorText: Brave and prideful, this Pokémon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.

attackEntries.name: Photon Laser
attackEntries.text: If you have 5 or more {P} Energy in play, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Wobbuffet
flavorText: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

attackEntries.name: Flip Over
attackEntries.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.
